    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-08-25T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-08-25T11:00:00-05:00" n="151"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d151">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">322.2222/2: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Ecuador</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dawson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Quito</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-08-25T11:00:00-05:00"
                            >August 25, 1931—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 3:30 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>41. Referring to my telegram No. 38. As city is quiet Dr. Ayora and his family
                    left the Legation this morning and returned to their home. They will return to
                    the Legation immediately if there is any reason to believe that their safety is
                    menaced.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dawson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
